            Title Quote
          Heading link



 
Copy link




The Voorhees Center is a dynamic resource center that engages residents, leaders, and policymakers seeking effective strategies for advancing community livability and vitality.














            Voorhees Welcomes Kevin Jackson as the Inaugural  Janet L. Smith Practitioner in Residence
          Heading link



 
Copy link



Kevin Jackson, Executive Director of the Chicago Rehab Network (CRN), is joining the Voorhees Center as our first Janet L. Smith Practitioner in Residence Online Giving To Voorhees Center! Kevin officially began his residency in August, and he will spend time at the Voorhees Center and CUPPA participating in research, technical assistance, and related programming.
A long-time friend of the late UIC Professor and the Voorhees Center Co-director Janet Smith, Kevin has led CRN since 1996. CRN is a citywide coalition of neighborhood and community-based development corporations dedicated to creating, preserving, and advocating for affordable housing in Chicago and beyond.


      Learn More About Kevin and the Chicago Rehab Network
    










